cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.IT 

The paper proposes a method for clustering evolving data points that lie on low-dimensional subspaces. This involves optimization frameworks, alternating minimization, and adaptive tuning of a smoothing parameter. The paper also discusses experiments on both synthetic and real-world datasets. Based on these factors, the most likely sub-categories are machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves optimization and data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT), which are less likely but still relevant sub-categories.
